The course is targetted at future teachers of English, but might also be useful for those who teach other languages through the medium of English. Participants analyse their own use of English in the classroom and read state-of.-the-art literature on the issue. The focus is on practical activities with the aim of learning the lexis that can be used at different stages of a lesson as well as while giving feedback to students.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop the participants' awareness of their own use of English in the classroom as well as their ability to conduct lessons in English and analyse classroom language use.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On successful completion of the course, the MA students will - explain why it is important to conduct English language classes in English; - analyse the teacher's use of English in the classroom using conversation analysis; - use appropriate English for classroom management, for communicating lesson content and for giving feedback to students.
